05/11/2002
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina -- The international community's High Representative in BiH, Paddy Ashdown, said Monday (4 November) that he expects preliminary findings on the investigation into the Orao aviation factory's arms sales to Iraq to be completed within a month, complete with names and potential penalties.
Meanwhile, Republika Srpska (RS) Prime Minister Mladen Ivanic told BiH public radio Monday that it appears a large number of institutions in the Federation of BiH (FBiH) were also involved in illegal trade with Iraq. He also admitted that RS recently negotiated the sale of a surplus of weapons to Burma.Negotiations, he said, halted after RS learned that Burma is under a UN embargo. (OHR Sources, Oslobodjenje, Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine, Dnevni List, Glas Srpski - 05/11/02; BiH Radio 1, Sarajevo - 04/11/02)
